Merge pull request #47 in CLOUD/dashboard from develop to master

* commit '31c24c319cf15d6e81710cc20022b713e1676500': (62 commits)
  Sexier instructions

  isSoaJSService checks for SOAJS_PROFILE, SOAJS_ENV, and SOAJS_SERVICE_NAME env variables, not just SOAJS_PROFILE
  Show the service URL on the overview page
  extractDeploymentEnvironmentVariables()
  Width not full-width anymore
  Show code coverage for the `develop` branch, not `master`
  re-added required css… oops
  Removed console.logs
  `/coverages` page to see all repo’s test coverage, for admins only
  Fixed path to coverage metric
  Removed branch from Sonar key  (temporarily… not working in Sonar 6.3)
  Fixed deprecated endpoints of Sonar’s API
  Removed uptime accuracy notice
  Sonar metrics using repo branch as well
  Commented out failing tests... why are they failing when checking code coverage, but not when running tests only???
  More unit tests
  Fixed status page bug
  Status Page and Code Coverage: DONE!
  Using new status response, which is queries from DB directly
  ...
